## Why a Separate License Layer (なぜ独立した license layer か)

DISC-011 採択原則 (Codex Round 2):

These documents contain **scholarly editorial work** — analysis, framing,
discussion, and structural abstraction that is qualitatively different from
either functional code or factual data:

- multi-framework theoretical coexistence (DISC-007: structuralist /
  archetypal / ritual-functional / political-legitimacy)
- discussion provenance (who proposed what in Round 1/2/3)
- editorial discipline (CLAUDE.md governance rules)
- competing-interpretation overlays

Separating this license layer makes it explicit that **derivative works
remixing these interpretations must preserve attribution and share-alike**
to prevent stripping of:

- multi-framework caveats
- contradiction overlays
- editorial provenance
- epistemic neutrality discipline

## Important Notice: Editorial Interpretation, Not Authority (編纂解釈であり権威ではない)

DISC-011 採択 — Codex Round 2 最重要警告:

These documents are **editorial interpretation by the project's contributors
(human and AI-assisted)**. They are:

- ✅ scholarly analysis with explicit provenance
- ✅ multi-framework, multi-perspective, contradiction-tolerant
- ❌ NOT official shrine positions
- ❌ NOT academic consensus statements
- ❌ NOT government / religious authority pronouncements

The project maintains **epistemic neutrality** — refusing to be co-opted by
any political, religious, or scholarly faction (国家神道復活運動 /
排外主義 / 神話 literalism / pseudo-history への警戒、DISC-011 採択)。

## AI Contributor Disclosure (AI 寄稿者開示)

Per DISC-011 採択原則, contributors must disclose AI involvement levels:

- `human-written`: human-authored without AI assistance
- `AI-assisted`: human-authored with AI suggestions
- `AI-generated-reviewed`: AI-drafted, human-reviewed and edited
- `AI-generated`: AI-drafted, minimal human review (highest risk)

This disclosure is **part of the editorial provenance** and must be
preserved in derivatives.

See `CONTRIBUTING.md` for full contributor governance.

